{"id":14882004,"mediaExerciseId":"e9552892-a382-4aee-96ba-01dd8805fabe","exerciseName":"3","chapterName":"27","chapterTitle":"Leasing","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"27.3","sectionTitle":"Taxes, the IRS, and Leases","pageNumber":898,"solutions":[{"id":6356187,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to figure out why the IRS is so concerned about leasing. In addition, let us identify the standards that the IRS employs when analyzing a lease.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement 1 \n\n**IRS or Internal Revenue Service** is responsible for assisting the majority of taxpayers in complying with the tax law, while ensuring that the minority who refuse to comply pay their fair part. They are also in charge for collecting federal taxes and enforcing tax regulations.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"We will identify why IRS is concerned regarding leasing.\n\nThe IRS is concerned about leasing arrangements because they appear to be set up primarily to delay taxes at times.\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement 2\nThe standards that IRS employs in evaluating a lease are:\n\n- The lease should be used for business purposes\n- The lease shouldn't be use for the purpose of tax avoidance\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"be502bf8-5012-45e7-a294-c67a6b993ce8","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ro